<TITLE> Tk 252 mln proposed for ACC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)--The Anticorruption Commission will get an enhanced allocation in the new budget for FY 2010-11 aimed at giving a boost to the corruption-fighting agency. Under the budget proposal unveiled on Thursday, the ACC has been allocated Tk. 252.4 million, which is Tk. 6.4 million more than the current allocation of Tk. 246 million. Finance minister Abul Maal Abdul Muhith said in the budget speech that corruption was one of the main impediments to development and that is why the ACC allocation has been raised. "Good governance cannot be ensured without rooting out corruption." The minister said the cabinet approved a number of amendments to the ACC law to ensure effective prevention of corruption. He expressed his belief that the amendments would address the shortcomings in the existing law. He said the government wants the ACC remains independent but accountable. Muhith mentioned that they had introduced e-tendering to ensure transparency in public procurements. bdnews2
